        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 3:55PM PDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Basque Hills, or 29 miles north of Dufferena, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Basque Hills around 400 PM PDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
